Seiko 5 Sports Automatic Watch SRPD61 with its features:

Workpieces: The automatic movement of this Seiko 5 Sports consists of 169 workpieces

Automatic watch with manual winding and second-hand mechanism for convenient watch setting

Precise automatic movement Caliber: 4R36 analog

Jewels: 24 jewels

water resist: 10 bar

Watch glass: flat, scratch-resistant hard glass that is also well protected by the stainless steel bezel.

Dial color: green dial with stainless steel hour, minute hands and second hand

Dial: mounted, round stainless steel indexes with Lumibrite luminescent mass

Dial details: hour hand, minute hand and second hand coated with luminous material

Clasp: brushed stainless steel safety clasp with safety push button and Seiko lettering

Housing: matt polished stainless steel housing with screwed stainless steel bottom and glass bottom insert for viewing the automatic movement. Housing sides brushed matt

Vibrations: 6 beats per second / 21,600 beats per hour

Magnetic resistance: 4,800 A / m (amps / meter)

Function: hour, minute, second display, date and weekday in German and English display depending on the setting

Power reserve: approx. 41 hours power reserve

Bracelet: brushed stainless steel bracelet

Bracelet length: The stainless steel band has a length of approx. 205 mm incl. Fine adjustment

Bracelet width: 26.5 mm at the band stop

Weight: The Seiko 5 Sports Diver watch weighs about 190 grams

Case height: 13.4 mm

Case diameter (without crown) 42.5 mm

This 45.5 mm model in robust O-MEGASTEEL features a polished blue ceramic bezel with its diving scale in white enamel. Through the protuberant and domed sapphire crystal, the lacquered white dial has been given four Arabic numerals in blue, as well as 18K white gold hands and hour markers, which are all coated with white Super-LumiNova.





The watch is set on an O-MEGASTEEL bracelet with OMEGA’s patented extendable foldover rack-and-pusher with complementary length adjustment and extra diver extension, while on the caseback's Grade 5 titanium medallion, there is a laser-engraved Sonar emblem with the iconic OMEGA Seahorse at its centre. Inside, the watch is driven by the OMEGA Co-Axial Master Chronometer Calibre 8912.

The Oyster Perpetual 36mm with a turquoise blue dial and an Oyster bracelet.





The aesthetics of the Oyster Perpetual models set them apart as symbols of universal and classic style. They embody timeless form and function, firmly rooted in the pioneering origins of Rolex.





The sunray finish creates delicate light reflections on many dials in the Oyster Perpetual collection. It is obtained using masterful brushing techniques that create grooves running outwards from the centre of the dial. Light is diffused consistently along each engraving, creating a characteristic subtle glow that moves depending on the position of the wrist.
